## Best Practices

### Visual Variety
- **Don't**: Use "Title Only" for every slide
- **Do**: Alternate between "Title Only" and "Title Only_Alt"
- **Do**: Use "Section Title" to break up major sections
- **Do**: Use "1/2 Headline" for emphasis on key points

### Content Density
- **Less is more**: ~3-5 bullets per slide; for **2.8in** body boxes cap at **~5-6** short bullets
- **Font sizing**: Follow **`010-style-guide.mdc`** density rules (14pt default, 16pt sparse ≤3 bullets, 12pt dense >6 bullets)
- **White space**: Don\'t crowd the canvas; increase **`height_inches`** only when tables or charts need it. Never exceed 7-8 total lines of text per slide to prevent vertical overflow.

### Color Usage
- **Text**: Always use "ink" for main text (it's dark navy, works on light backgrounds)
- **Accents**: Use "ballpoint", "water_cooler", "blue_sky" sparingly for highlights
- **Never**: Use "paper" for text (it's too light)

### Icons
- Use Workday-approved icons from parse_template
- Center icons above related text: `center_in_width` = width of text below
- Typical 3-column layout: left_inches at 0.7, 3.4, 6.1 with center_in_width of 2.5

## Routing: 110 vs 130

**Use 110 (this rule) for:**
- Short decks (~10-20 slides)
- Executive briefings
- PRD summaries
- Competitive intelligence readouts (non-PMF)
- Product updates
- Strategy presentations
- Meeting readouts
- Customer presentations

**Use 130 (not 110) for:**
- Full PMF roadmap decks (36-50 slides)
- Country/regional PMF analysis presentations
- PESTEL + primary research + thematic analysis structure
- Decks matching `docs/decks/gcc-pmf-roadmap-baseline-slides-spec.md`
- When user says "match v65", "GCC PMF deck", "country PMF roadmap"

If unsure, check with user or orchestrator.

